1
00:00:00,360 --> 00:00:03,360
Tim and I will probably be busy with
preparing for the wedding next week.

2
00:00:03,640 --> 00:00:04,480
I’ll try to be there.

3
00:00:04,480 --> 00:00:08,120
Give me one last hug
and we have ourselves a fair deal.

4
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:10,800
I’m giving you back the 250 million.

5
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:11,960
We’re getting a divorce.

6
00:00:12,280 --> 00:00:14,320
I don’t want anything from you, North.

7
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:19,360
Somebody as nice as you
would never hurt me.

8
00:00:19,640 --> 00:00:21,440
I’ll go.

9
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:22,680
Wait.

10
00:00:24,280 --> 00:00:26,200
You said you wouldn’t give up.

11
00:00:31,560 --> 00:00:32,920
How the hell did it turn out like that?

12
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:37,600
Honestly, I think it’s because
North still has feelings for me.

13
00:00:40,240 --> 00:00:41,040
What about you?

14
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:42,640
Aren’t you getting married?

15
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:47,560
What?

16
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:48,920
Why aren’t you dancing on air?

17
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:49,800
What’s wrong?

18
00:00:50,080 --> 00:00:51,040
I’m happy.

19
00:00:51,640 --> 00:00:52,720
I’m just figuring something out.

20
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:54,880
Oom can’t be at my wedding anymore.

21
00:00:55,560 --> 00:00:55,920
What?

22
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:57,800
Why not?

23
00:00:59,040 --> 00:01:00,840
That’s some nerve you got there
asking me that.

24
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:02,520
Did you forget the same mom incident?

25
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:04,760
Oh, yeah.

26
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:06,360
You’re right.

27
00:01:06,360 --> 00:01:09,800
My plan was that
I’d hire Oom as my mother,

28
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:13,920
so she could keep everyone who plays
my relatives and groomsmen in check.

29
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:16,600
But now that she can’t be there,
everything is derailed.

30
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:20,880
How about you let me help you?

31
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:22,640
I’m good at this, you know.

32
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:24,840
It’s too risky.

33
00:01:25,520 --> 00:01:26,920
Tim, listen to me.

34
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:29,320
I only know a handful of people.

35
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:33,280
You, North, Ms. Nana, and Mr. Pai.

36
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:35,840
Keeping a low profile at the wedding

37
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:37,200
wouldn’t be difficult for me.

38
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:38,560
It’s easy-breezy.

39
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:41,440
But I think—

40
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,440
Don’t say no.

41
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:45,160
Believe me.

42
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:47,480
I’m the perfect guy for the job.

43
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:50,560
I swear anyone else you hire
would turn their back on you.

44
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:52,040
But not me.

45
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:53,440
Alright?

46
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:56,240
Fine.

47
00:01:56,560 --> 00:02:02,560
What did you tell Mr. Pai
about Oom, though?

48
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:10,520
I really need to apologize
to you and Pai, love

49
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:13,120
I’m in London right now,

50
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:14,800
and I don’t feel very well.

51
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:16,840
I don’t think I can fly back in time.

52
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:18,400
It’s alright, Mom.

53
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:21,360
I’ll see you when you feel better.

54
00:02:27,160 --> 00:02:27,640
Mom.

55
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:28,840
Mom?
Mom

56
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:31,440
Mom, the connection’s not good.

57
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:33,760
I’ll hang up and we’ll talk soon.

58
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:35,080
Take a rest, Mom.

59
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:35,680
Bye.

60
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,600
Ugh, what a drag.

61
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,280
I hope you don’t mind,

62
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,920
but I’m taking a few of these home.

63
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:57,680
It’s too bad.

64
00:02:58,520 --> 00:02:59,360
Yeah.

65
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:01,520
But there’s nothing we can do.

66
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,680
I’ll go get ready.

67
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,160
We have so many things
to sort out at the hotel.

68
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:13,520
Are you getting nervous, baby?

69
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:14,520
Yeah.

70
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:17,160
I got all anxious about it all of a sudden.

71
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:19,040
We’re getting married soon.

72
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:23,800
You don’t have to be.

73
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:25,680
How about this?

74
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,640
I’ll be there for you.

75
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:30,280
I’ll be a groom, too.

76
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:32,000
You won’t have to do it all alone.

77
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:32,920
That sounds good?
Umm.

78
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,080
Alright?

79
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:37,080
Alright?
Alright

80
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:39,200
Nervous, are you?

81
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:40,400
I’m gonna take a shower.

82
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,280
No need to be nervous.

83
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:30,800
Oh, Kuea.

84
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:32,440
Hey, Pai.

85
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:36,560
You can wait in the groomsmen’s
waiting room over there, Mr. Kuea.

86
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:37,480
Of course.

87
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:38,840
See you.
Good luck.

88
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,720
This way, Mr. Pai.

89
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,080
The venue is upstairs, sir.

90
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:00,480
Please.
Over there.

91
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:03,640
Hello, Ms. Nana.

92
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,760
Right. I’m here.

93
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,160
Where should I wait?

94
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:08,760
Should I…

95
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:20,400
I’m alright.

96
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:21,720
Yes.

97
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:43,040
All done, sir.

98
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,240
Thank you.

99
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,440
Can you excuse me for a minute?

100
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:34,840
Ms. Nana.
Yes?

101
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:37,120
Do you happen to have
a necklace for me to borrow?

102
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:39,560
I want to be at the gold and silver gates.

103
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:41,360
Mr. North,

104
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:45,040
there’s no gold and silver gates
at a Chinese wedding procession.

105
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:46,520
Oww.

106
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:48,120
There goes my extra pocket money.

107
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,040
I’m here.

108
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:53,080
Right.

109
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:54,960
Thank you.

110
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,720
I’ll take it from here.

111
00:07:57,880 --> 00:08:01,480
Mr. North, please wait in the hall
with all your relatives, sir.

112
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:02,480
As for Mr. Tim…
Yes?

113
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:03,840
Please follow me.

114
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:04,600
Of course.

115
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:08,160
Best of luck, Tim.

116
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:08,840
Thanks.

117
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:15,760
I wonder how much that is.

118
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:20,040
I heard it’s 69 million.

119
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,760
It’s Mr. Tim’s whole life savings.

120
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:24,880
I see.

121
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:28,400
I’m sorry.

122
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:32,200
You have the same build
as my boyfriend’s.

123
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:34,240
I…

124
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:37,240
I was careless.

125
00:08:37,640 --> 00:08:38,120
Sorry.

126
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:43,800
It’s alright.

127
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,680
Excuse me.

128
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:46,800
Bye.

129
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:57,000
Ho, hi ho hi ho hi ho…

130
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:59,440
- Hew!
- Hew!

131
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:09,920
Ho, hi ho hi ho hi ho…

132
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:11,720
Hew!

133
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:16,080
Let’s go.

134
00:10:42,920 --> 00:10:47,560
Please give a round of applause
to our newlyweds!

135
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:55,880
Mr. Tim, please pick up the ring.

136
00:10:55,920 --> 00:11:01,360
You can now put it on
Mr. Pai’s left ring finger.

137
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:05,440
Mr. Pai, please pick up the ring.

138
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:08,480
Please put it on Mr. Tim’s left ring finger.

139
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:11,000
And from this moment on,

140
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:16,280
Mr. Thanin Chaiyanuwat and
Mr. Jirachote Jeeramongkolthanun

141
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:18,760
are now husbands.

142
00:11:18,760 --> 00:11:20,920
Please give them
another round of applause.

143
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:03,200
MARRIAGE CERTIFICATE

144
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:18,520
To sanctify their love,

145
00:12:18,520 --> 00:12:20,800
in front of all of us as witnesses,

146
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:25,040
what should the newlyweds do?

147
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:28,960
- Kiss!
- Kiss!

148
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:30,440
That is loud and clear.

149
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:31,720
So please, kiss!

150
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:34,160
In one,

151
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:36,280
two,

152
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:39,840
three.

153
00:12:54,360 --> 00:13:00,400
The newlyweds will now visit each table
to show their gratitude for your attendance.

154
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:03,000
Another round of applause, please.

155
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:08,880
Hey.

156
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:10,160
I’m gonna go grab some wine.

157
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:10,960
You want anything?

158
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:12,360
One for me as well.

159
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:15,320
White wine, please.

160
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:16,800
I hope the food is to your liking.

161
00:13:19,680 --> 00:13:20,120
Hello.

162
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:22,360
Hi.

163
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:25,360
I can’t help but wonder if you have
a drinking partner tonight.

164
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,320
Uhh…

165
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:29,520
I’m Tim’s groomsman.

166
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:30,680
I see.

167
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:32,200
I’m Pai’s cousin.

168
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:33,240
I see.

169
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:34,880
What are you drinki—

170
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:36,760
Crap.
Are you alright?

171
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:38,960
Please let me know…

172
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:40,680
Careful, boy!

173
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:43,440
Stay away from my boyfriend.

174
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:47,560
Hey—

175
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:53,040
Excuse me.

176
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,160
Pai.

177
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:03,560
What are you doing here?
What do you want?

178
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:08,200
I…

179
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,280
North, did you know about this?

180
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:11,400
I didn’t.

181
00:14:11,480 --> 00:14:12,600
This is the first time I saw him.

182
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:14,680
Mr. Pai, I can explain.

183
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:15,760
Go on, then.

184
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:22,160
What are you doing here, U?

185
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:22,840
I…
What do you want now?

186
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:24,920
What happened?

187
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,400
I missed North.

188
00:14:31,760 --> 00:14:32,760
Are you out of your mind?

189
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:33,880
You broke up.

190
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:34,960
What would you want to see him for?

191
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:36,040
I couldn’t stop myself.

192
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:37,960
Pai, let me deal with this.

193
00:14:38,040 --> 00:14:39,200
North, take your brother and go.

194
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:40,400
Come here.
- I didn’t—
- Just come on.

195
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:42,280
Forget it.

196
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:45,560
North.

197
00:14:46,520 --> 00:14:47,800
Are you sure you didn’t know about this?

198
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:49,400
I really didn’t.

199
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:50,880
I found out the same way you did.

200
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:52,640
Mr. Pai, sir.

201
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:56,640
Mr. Pai.

202
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,240
My name is Airy.

203
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:05,040
And we have something
we’d like to tell you, Mr. Pai.

204
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:10,920
Ms. Airy.

205
00:15:11,440 --> 00:15:12,400
Please, Ms. Airy.

206
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:13,160
Ms. Airy.
Ms. Airy.

207
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:15,480
Let’s talk outside.

208
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:16,800
Let go of me.

209
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:19,120
Please listen to me.

210
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:20,480
Why don’t we talk outside?

211
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:21,840
Please, let’s talk.

212
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:24,440
Please.

213
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:30,360
Mr. Pai, we are all here to tell you the truth

214
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:33,400
about what your groom did to us.

215
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:35,720
Tim?

216
00:15:38,320 --> 00:15:39,000
What’s going on?

217
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:42,040
I can explain, Pai.

218
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:43,600
There’s actually nothing serious.

219
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:44,760
Let’s talk outside.

220
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:47,240
It’s better if you hear it from us, Mr. Pai.

221
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:52,160
Last week, Hong and I—

222
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:53,920
Oh, I’m mistaken.

223
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:57,240
Tim and I… We just broke up.

224
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:08,480
If I didn’t get suspicious,

225
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:14,160
I wouldn’t have found out
what an awful man your groom is.

226
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:15,840
Tell me everything.

227
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:20,360
He’s here with different women every day.

228
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:22,120
You’re not the only one.

229
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:28,280
What you don’t know is that
Tim was going out with all of us.

230
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:36,840
When I said he was going out
with all of us,

231
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:38,480
I did mean that he was cheating on you,

232
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:42,040
while getting more than 10 million
in total out of all of us.

233
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:48,040
Is that true…

234
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:50,200
Tim?

235
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:58,480
Tell me it isn’t true.

236
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:02,400
Tell him, Tim.

237
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:04,720
Or is it Hong?

238
00:17:05,080 --> 00:17:07,080
Or is it Mek?

239
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:08,520
Or is it Vee?

240
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:09,320
Please, stop, Airy.

241
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:10,960
I’ll admit it.

242
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:12,800
I’m sorry.

243
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:15,920
You think an apology is enough?

244
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:19,120
I’m not suing you today.

245
00:17:19,520 --> 00:17:21,680
But I’ll at least do this!

246
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,280
Girls, get him!

247
00:17:24,360 --> 00:17:25,080
Security!

248
00:17:25,080 --> 00:17:27,480
Make him pay for all the money
he took from us!

249
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:30,000
I don’t remember!

250
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:31,400
I’m sorry!

251
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:36,560
No photos, please!

252
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:48,960
Pai.

253
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:52,400
Pai.

254
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:57,880
Pai, hear me out.

255
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:01,160
Pai.

256
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:02,920
Pai.

257
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:05,920
Pai.

258
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:30,400
Hey.

259
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:32,280
You awake?

260
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:34,560
How are you feeling?

261
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:42,880
What happened?

262
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:48,640
One of your girls threw
a wine bottle at you.

263
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,960
It knocked you out.

264
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:54,520
I didn’t know what to do
so I took you to the hospital.

265
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:56,240
You’re alright, though.

266
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:58,480
The doctor said you should just
take a rest and you’ll be fine.

267
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:03,640
Hey, hey, hey.

268
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:05,360
You don’t need to get up so soon.

269
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:12,120
Where’s Pai?

270
00:20:14,320 --> 00:20:16,680
Is that the only thing
on your mind right now?

271
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:17,760
Mr. Pai?

272
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:19,640
Worry about yourself first.

273
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:25,240
Tim!

274
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:27,960
Tim, what would the doctor say?

275
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:30,640
Tim!

276
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:37,400
That’s everything I know.

277
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:44,400
You and Mr. North had no idea
Mr. Tim is a con artist?

278
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:46,880
As we said,

279
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:49,520
we only learned that about U.

280
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:54,040
As for Tim… We had no clue.

281
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:05,280
Ugh.

282
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:06,840
What a mess.

283
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:09,600
Da Zhan, don’t play with that.

284
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:53,080
I’ve heard everything from our lawyers.

285
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:56,880
Let me talk to Pai.

286
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:05,080
You two, stay.

287
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,560
The rest of you, go and wait outside.

288
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:25,640
Pai.

289
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:30,600
How will you take responsibility for this?

290
00:22:44,360 --> 00:22:49,240
I admit it was because
I wasn’t being careful.

291
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:54,960
I’m willing to pay for everything.

292
00:22:56,960 --> 00:22:58,160
But I ask for one thing…

293
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:06,240
Call me if anything comes up, alright?

294
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:08,480
Of course, Auntie.

295
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:14,760
Da Zhan, wake up, dear.

296
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:17,080
Let’s go and take you to bed.

297
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:29,720
North.

298
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:30,840
Where is Pai?

299
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:37,160
He’s getting lectured by Grandpa in there.

300
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:38,720
- Hey, hey!
- Tim.

301
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:39,840
Do not enter, sir.

302
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:40,400
Why not?

303
00:23:41,480 --> 00:23:44,640
Wait out here quietly with me
if you don’t have a death wish.

304
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:46,960
I have to see Pai.

305
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:47,680
You can’t.

306
00:23:47,680 --> 00:23:49,160
U, let go of me!

307
00:23:49,160 --> 00:23:49,640
Please.
Pai!

308
00:23:51,280 --> 00:23:51,680
Tim.

309
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:53,280
Let go of me!
Pai!

310
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:54,360
What’s the ruckus?

311
00:23:54,920 --> 00:23:55,200
Pai.

312
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:56,840
Pai.

313
00:23:57,640 --> 00:23:58,480
What are you doing here?

314
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:00,880
Don’t show your face here again.

315
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:02,640
Both of you.

316
00:24:06,360 --> 00:24:07,160
Baby, listen to—
Don’t call me “baby.”

317
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:09,880
I don’t even know who you are.

318
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:12,960
Pai.

319
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:14,800
Please calm down and listen to me.

320
00:24:16,520 --> 00:24:17,360
I won’t sue you,

321
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:20,080
or press any charges.

322
00:24:23,640 --> 00:24:25,440
I only ask that you both leave us alone.

323
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:34,320
What do you mean
you won’t press charges?

324
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:37,960
I talked to Grandpa.

325
00:24:42,440 --> 00:24:43,320
I admit it was because

326
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:47,200
I wasn’t being careful.

327
00:24:49,840 --> 00:24:52,240
I’m willing to pay for everything.

328
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:55,120
But I ask for one thing…

329
00:24:57,560 --> 00:25:00,120
Please don’t press charges
or sue both Tim and U.

330
00:25:00,400 --> 00:25:01,640
Pai?

331
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:07,560
To preserve our family’s reputation and
to reassure Empire’s businesses,

332
00:25:10,360 --> 00:25:14,080
I will resign as the CEO of Empire.

333
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:17,160
Do you think your resignation
will fix anything?

334
00:25:29,840 --> 00:25:31,960
Well, then…

335
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:36,320
Cut me loose from this family.

336
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:41,760
I want nothing to do with this family.

337
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:48,800
I will not spend the money or use the
privileges from my previous role at work.

338
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:51,440
Will that…

339
00:25:53,600 --> 00:25:54,600
be enough for you?

340
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:01,960
I’m useless to you now.

341
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:07,680
So, please…

342
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:12,360
Just get out of my life.

343
00:26:59,120 --> 00:26:59,560
Pai.
Pai.

344
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:37,240
Pai, wait.
Tim.

345
00:27:37,920 --> 00:27:38,440
Mr. Pai.
Tim.

346
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:40,480
Mr. Pai.

347
00:27:41,480 --> 00:27:42,240
Let him be.

348
00:27:42,720 --> 00:27:43,840
You can talk to him later.

349
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:55,160
Grandpa can’t do this.

350
00:27:56,120 --> 00:27:57,760
How could he disown Pai?

351
00:27:57,760 --> 00:27:58,320
North!

352
00:27:59,240 --> 00:28:02,920
You two are not allowed
to help him in any way!

353
00:28:06,600 --> 00:28:08,120
How could you do this, Grandpa?

354
00:28:09,560 --> 00:28:11,640
If you’re going to disown Pai,

355
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:13,360
you might as well disown me too!

356
00:28:13,360 --> 00:28:15,240
I don’t want Pai to take responsibility
for this alone.

357
00:28:15,720 --> 00:28:16,440
North!

358
00:28:16,440 --> 00:28:19,520
You never scold me
when I do something wrong.

359
00:28:20,360 --> 00:28:22,480
I’m not done dealing with this.

360
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:23,480
I don’t care.

361
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:26,240
You have no right to do this to Pai.

362
00:28:27,240 --> 00:28:28,360
If you disown Pai,

363
00:28:29,120 --> 00:28:30,280
I won’t talk to you again!

364
00:28:31,160 --> 00:28:31,600
Good!

365
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:34,600
Then you can both go, the lot of you!

366
00:28:35,800 --> 00:28:38,600
Seize both of their credit cards,

367
00:28:39,080 --> 00:28:40,600
as well as their bank accounts.

368
00:28:40,600 --> 00:28:42,080
Take back every single car,

369
00:28:42,080 --> 00:28:43,360
and every single home,

370
00:28:43,360 --> 00:28:44,880
and all of their assets.

371
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:48,360
They will go with nothing but
the clothes on their backs.

372
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:20,760
North?

373
00:29:23,360 --> 00:29:24,360
What happened?

374
00:29:24,960 --> 00:29:26,600
How come you’re locked out, too?

375
00:29:27,840 --> 00:29:28,600
I…

376
00:29:29,320 --> 00:29:31,080
I put up a fight against Grandpa…

377
00:29:31,600 --> 00:29:32,720
For you.

378
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:37,440
I guess I’m also disowned now.

379
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:40,720
North.

380
00:29:41,160 --> 00:29:42,520
Why would you do that?

381
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:46,480
I can take care of myself if I’m on my own,

382
00:29:47,080 --> 00:29:48,640
but you…

383
00:29:49,080 --> 00:29:50,840
I don’t know if I can take care of you.

384
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:53,440
It’s alright.

385
00:29:53,480 --> 00:29:54,960
As long as we have each other,

386
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:56,440
I know we can do it.

387
00:30:04,960 --> 00:30:07,240
You’re locked out, too?

388
00:30:11,160 --> 00:30:13,680
I guess Grandpa won’t even
let us pack our bags.

389
00:30:33,640 --> 00:30:36,560
I told you I don’t want to see
you two again.

390
00:30:36,640 --> 00:30:37,960
Don’t you understand?

391
00:30:39,160 --> 00:30:40,120
I do.

392
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:42,600
But I still want to see you.

393
00:30:45,760 --> 00:30:48,440
So I don’t think I can do
what you told me to.

394
00:30:49,840 --> 00:30:50,840
Mr. Pai.

395
00:30:51,160 --> 00:30:53,200
We really want to help you and North.

396
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:54,640
What can you do?

397
00:30:55,120 --> 00:30:56,920
Did you not cause
enough problems already?

398
00:30:57,560 --> 00:30:59,360
I can take care of myself.

399
00:30:59,360 --> 00:31:01,040
Can you drop the tough guy act for a sec?

400
00:31:07,520 --> 00:31:09,680
You don’t have to act like
you’re strong in front of me.

401
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:12,280
I know you’re exhausted.

402
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:23,000
Let me take care of you.

403
00:31:24,360 --> 00:31:26,000
Once you’re back on your feet,

404
00:31:26,360 --> 00:31:27,680
we can go from there.

405
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:33,440
Pai.

406
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:34,800
Please.

407
00:31:37,760 --> 00:31:38,840
I have a house.

408
00:31:40,720 --> 00:31:42,240
It’s big enough for all of us.

409
00:31:45,120 --> 00:31:46,640
Let’s stay there for now.

410
00:31:47,160 --> 00:31:48,680
We can work the rest out later.

411
00:31:50,360 --> 00:31:51,560
Listen to me.

412
00:31:52,560 --> 00:31:54,720
I will never step foot in your house.

413
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:06,760
How about you staying at my place?

414
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:09,640
North and I will stay at Tim’s.

415
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:15,640
You don’t have much choice
today, you know?

416
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:16,880
Just shut your mouth.

417
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:23,440
Let’s go, then.

418
00:32:23,520 --> 00:32:24,920
What are we waiting for?

419
00:32:32,520 --> 00:32:33,160
Let’s go.

420
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:36,080
Pai.

421
00:32:36,840 --> 00:32:37,480
Pai!

422
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:51,520
You and North stay here tonight.

423
00:32:51,840 --> 00:32:54,840
We’ll sort things out tomorrow morning.

424
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:57,000
Thank you.

425
00:32:58,000 --> 00:32:59,000
Tim.

426
00:33:00,120 --> 00:33:01,280
Can I talk to you for a bit?

427
00:33:03,600 --> 00:33:06,040
Can you wait outside?

428
00:33:08,720 --> 00:33:09,320
Sure.

429
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:10,760
Don’t take long.

430
00:33:13,440 --> 00:33:14,440
I’m scared of ghosts.

431
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:15,600
Come on.
We’ll be a minute.

432
00:33:16,280 --> 00:33:16,640
Please.

433
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:29,440
I don’t know what this was all about.

434
00:33:30,600 --> 00:33:31,480
But…

435
00:33:32,440 --> 00:33:34,560
Are you in love with Pai?

436
00:33:40,040 --> 00:33:43,360
If I say yes, will you believe me?

437
00:33:52,240 --> 00:33:53,080
Okay.

438
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:55,520
That’s all I need to hear.

439
00:33:57,480 --> 00:33:59,280
You should go to Pai.

440
00:34:03,480 --> 00:34:04,440
Tim.

441
00:34:07,960 --> 00:34:09,680
Don’t fool him again.

442
00:34:10,120 --> 00:34:11,320
I’m begging you.

443
00:34:15,680 --> 00:34:18,680
I promise I won’t lie to him again.

444
00:34:31,880 --> 00:34:32,680
North.

445
00:34:33,160 --> 00:34:35,760
I think this place is haunted.

446
00:34:38,160 --> 00:34:39,480
Don’t be ridiculous.

447
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:40,680
- I mean it!
- Just go take a shower.

448
00:35:00,240 --> 00:35:01,280
U.

449
00:35:01,920 --> 00:35:02,760
Hmm?

450
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:08,120
Can you get in bed with me?

451
00:35:08,120 --> 00:35:09,880
I’m scared of ghosts.

452
00:35:13,520 --> 00:35:15,520
You were just calling me ridiculous.

453
00:35:16,600 --> 00:35:18,800
Well, you kept mentioning ghosts!

454
00:35:20,040 --> 00:35:21,000
Come on.

455
00:35:22,640 --> 00:35:23,480
Of course.

456
00:35:40,240 --> 00:35:41,240
U…

457
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:42,840
Hmm?

458
00:35:47,080 --> 00:35:49,520
Did you know about Tim before?

459
00:35:58,640 --> 00:35:59,560
U!

460
00:36:01,360 --> 00:36:02,520
I’m sorry.

461
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:09,120
I actually got to know Tim after I met you.

462
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:13,920
He and I clocked each other
the minute we locked eyes.

463
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:24,480
So we promised to have each other’s back
if we didn’t betray each other.

464
00:36:27,240 --> 00:36:29,600
You conmen are unbelievable.

465
00:36:29,920 --> 00:36:30,880
Look at us.

466
00:36:31,560 --> 00:36:33,120
None of us has anything
to our names now.

467
00:36:37,560 --> 00:36:41,520
I have nothing for you
to swindle off of me anymore.

468
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:47,920
So if you want to leave,
this is when you make a run for it.

469
00:36:52,720 --> 00:36:53,600
North.

470
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:55,280
I’m not going anywhere.

471
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:58,720
I brought you here.

472
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:01,840
I have to take responsibility.

473
00:37:04,760 --> 00:37:05,360
Come.

474
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:08,360
Come here.

475
00:37:13,080 --> 00:37:14,840
I won’t let you go through this.

476
00:37:16,520 --> 00:37:20,320
I promise everything will be alright.

477
00:37:59,400 --> 00:38:01,000
I’ve brought you a change of clothes.

478
00:38:07,920 --> 00:38:09,520
Well, at least he took it.

479
00:38:51,600 --> 00:38:52,360
Help!
Pai, what’s happened?

480
00:38:53,280 --> 00:38:54,200
Pai!

481
00:38:56,400 --> 00:38:57,000
That hurts!

482
00:38:57,880 --> 00:38:58,400
Pai!
Pai, what’s wrong?

483
00:38:59,000 --> 00:38:59,480
Pai!
What’s happened?

484
00:39:00,080 --> 00:39:01,240
Gecko!

485
00:39:01,640 --> 00:39:02,240
Where?

486
00:39:02,920 --> 00:39:03,520
Where is it?

487
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:06,360
Gecko! It’s in my shirt!

488
00:39:06,360 --> 00:39:08,000
It’s in my shirt!

489
00:39:17,080 --> 00:39:17,880
What you looking at?
Get out!

490
00:39:21,440 --> 00:39:22,560
I’m here to save you, you know?

491
00:39:22,720 --> 00:39:25,560
What happens
if another gecko falls on you?

492
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:28,600
I was only taken by surprise.

493
00:39:28,600 --> 00:39:30,040
But I’m more cautious now.

494
00:39:30,160 --> 00:39:31,000
I can take care of myself.
Get out!

495
00:39:32,920 --> 00:39:34,040
Alright, good boy.

496
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:36,120
Don’t shout for help
if you see another one.

497
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:38,720
That’s scary.

498
00:39:42,840 --> 00:39:43,840
Put a shirt back on.

499
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:44,880
I’ll take you to breakfast.

500
00:39:45,280 --> 00:39:45,880
No need.

501
00:39:45,920 --> 00:39:47,040
I’m more than capable of
having breakfast on my own.

502
00:39:47,040 --> 00:39:47,640
Get out!

503
00:39:54,280 --> 00:39:56,520
GRANDMA’S MADE-TO-ORDER

504
00:40:00,600 --> 00:40:01,240
Hello.
Hey, U.

505
00:40:02,760 --> 00:40:03,840
A table for how many people?

506
00:40:03,840 --> 00:40:04,600
Three, please.

507
00:40:07,440 --> 00:40:08,200
Sit down.

508
00:40:26,880 --> 00:40:27,960
Table for one, sir.

509
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:40,960
Pai.

510
00:40:42,120 --> 00:40:46,880
(Next up, let’s see a pregnant
mother cow in Khon Khaen.)

511
00:40:46,880 --> 00:40:50,760
(Cows normally carry their pregnancy
to nine months…)

512
00:40:50,760 --> 00:40:54,640
I thought the wedding yesterday
would be on every channel.

513
00:40:57,200 --> 00:40:58,960
Grandpa would never allow it.

514
00:40:59,240 --> 00:41:01,320
I’m sure he paid them a hefty sum
to cover up the news.

515
00:41:03,200 --> 00:41:05,760
We’re lucky it’s not a scandal.

516
00:41:06,160 --> 00:41:07,960
Most people wouldn’t know,

517
00:41:07,960 --> 00:41:10,280
but our business partners
must have learned about it.

518
00:41:10,800 --> 00:41:13,320
They’re probably only keeping it quiet
for the sake of manners.

519
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:18,680
Can we please order?

520
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:30,080
GRANDMA’S MADE-TO-ORDER

521
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:32,800
Help me out.

522
00:41:42,240 --> 00:41:43,680
How is it, Mr. Pai?

523
00:41:43,920 --> 00:41:45,040
Are you full?

524
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:46,240
Please enjoy yourself.

525
00:41:46,240 --> 00:41:47,520
This meal is on me.

526
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:50,480
It’s your responsibility anyway.

527
00:41:53,160 --> 00:41:54,280
You’re right.

528
00:41:56,000 --> 00:41:56,920
Tim told me—

529
00:41:56,920 --> 00:41:59,080
Don’t say that name in front of me.

530
00:42:04,440 --> 00:42:05,360
Of course.

531
00:42:05,720 --> 00:42:12,440
A thief told me you had an encounter
with a house gecko in my room.

532
00:42:16,840 --> 00:42:18,120
I’m really sorry about that, Mr. Pai.

533
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:20,600
My place is actually crawling with geck—

534
00:42:20,600 --> 00:42:22,360
Stop talking about house geckos.

535
00:42:24,480 --> 00:42:26,240
Just say what you want to say.

536
00:42:30,320 --> 00:42:33,200
Shouldn’t you stay with us?

537
00:42:34,040 --> 00:42:35,240
Yeah, Pai.

538
00:42:35,240 --> 00:42:36,520
Move into the house.

539
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:38,960
We slept like a rock last night.

540
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:40,800
Come on.

541
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:02,720
I’ll put your things upstairs.

542
00:43:14,280 --> 00:43:15,560
You two.

543
00:43:17,160 --> 00:43:18,640
Can I talk to you?

544
00:43:21,600 --> 00:43:22,840
What about?

545
00:43:23,920 --> 00:43:25,800
Did you really get a divorce?

546
00:43:26,080 --> 00:43:27,800
Or did you fool me, too?

547
00:43:28,840 --> 00:43:30,560
We really got a divorce.

548
00:43:30,880 --> 00:43:32,200
If you did,

549
00:43:32,600 --> 00:43:34,360
how come you’re still clinging
to each other like that?

550
00:43:37,240 --> 00:43:39,520
You ever heard of ‘a slip of the hand’?

551
00:43:40,920 --> 00:43:42,280
Don’t be ridiculous.

552
00:43:43,280 --> 00:43:46,280
U, tell me and be succinct.

553
00:43:49,360 --> 00:43:51,040
North and I really are divorced.

554
00:43:51,040 --> 00:43:53,120
I was going to leave him.

555
00:43:53,120 --> 00:43:54,600
I even packed my bag.

556
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:58,480
But North looked like
he was on the verge of tears,

557
00:43:58,920 --> 00:44:03,480
and then jumped into my arms,
and kissed me.

558
00:44:05,040 --> 00:44:06,560
So we…

559
00:44:06,560 --> 00:44:07,640
Slept together.

560
00:44:08,600 --> 00:44:09,160
U!

561
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:16,720
‘Slip of the hand,’ you know?

562
00:44:16,720 --> 00:44:17,440
Enough.

563
00:44:17,800 --> 00:44:18,720
I’ve heard enough.

564
00:44:18,720 --> 00:44:19,840
I’m going to take a nap.

565
00:44:25,280 --> 00:44:25,880
Hey!

566
00:44:26,400 --> 00:44:27,440
Where’s my room?

567
00:44:28,200 --> 00:44:29,960
Come upstairs and find out.

568
00:44:30,280 --> 00:44:32,040
You complain a lot, don’t you?

569
00:44:32,280 --> 00:44:34,040
And he nags a lot, too.

570
00:44:36,800 --> 00:44:37,360
North.

571
00:44:38,720 --> 00:44:39,680
Yes?

572
00:44:41,320 --> 00:44:44,480
Actually, I haven’t talked to you about this.

573
00:44:46,680 --> 00:44:47,480
What?

574
00:44:50,200 --> 00:44:52,400
Let’s start over.

575
00:44:54,680 --> 00:44:56,120
Start over?

576
00:44:59,120 --> 00:45:03,120
Let’s start over and go out properly.

577
00:45:04,720 --> 00:45:07,240
Let’s keep no secrets from each other.

578
00:45:07,520 --> 00:45:09,040
No paranoia.

579
00:45:09,240 --> 00:45:10,760
No con this time.

580
00:45:19,280 --> 00:45:20,160
Let’s do it.

581
00:45:21,280 --> 00:45:21,800
Yes!

582
00:45:22,160 --> 00:45:23,320
Under one condition.

583
00:45:25,400 --> 00:45:26,480
What is it?

584
00:45:28,560 --> 00:45:33,400
Please don’t lie to me again from now on,
no matter what it’s about.

585
00:45:34,200 --> 00:45:35,040
Agreed.

586
00:45:42,480 --> 00:45:43,160
Okay.

587
00:46:00,320 --> 00:46:01,600
You can sleep here.

588
00:46:02,360 --> 00:46:04,080
I promise there are no geckos.

589
00:46:05,400 --> 00:46:05,840
Here.

590
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:13,840
What happened to you?

591
00:46:14,320 --> 00:46:15,000
Oh?

592
00:46:15,360 --> 00:46:16,040
This?

593
00:46:16,560 --> 00:46:19,480
Someone threw a wine bottle at my head.

594
00:46:20,880 --> 00:46:22,880
As for this on my hand,

595
00:46:23,080 --> 00:46:25,520
I shoved the IV off when
I needed to get out of the hospital.

596
00:46:26,600 --> 00:46:28,520
You were at the hospital?

597
00:46:29,320 --> 00:46:30,600
Why did you leave?

598
00:46:32,120 --> 00:46:35,120
I left because I was worried about you.

599
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:39,800
I didn’t want you to go through
the mess I made on your own.

600
00:46:43,840 --> 00:46:47,800
You should get the wounds dressed
if you don’t want an infection.

601
00:46:50,240 --> 00:46:51,520
Worried about me?

602
00:46:52,320 --> 00:46:54,560
Can you help me with it?

603
00:46:57,120 --> 00:46:58,280
Why don’t you take care of yourself?

604
00:46:58,280 --> 00:46:58,720
Go.

605
00:48:09,600 --> 00:48:14,360
TIM AND PAI’S HOME PROJECT

606
00:48:49,840 --> 00:48:51,560
I really did study architecture.

607
00:48:56,160 --> 00:48:57,280
Why are you so spooked?

608
00:48:57,880 --> 00:48:59,360
This house really isn’t haunted.

609
00:48:59,360 --> 00:49:00,600
Don’t worry about that.

610
00:49:01,920 --> 00:49:03,160
It’s not ghosts I’m afraid of.

611
00:49:03,840 --> 00:49:05,760
I’m more worried about getting haunted
by someone who’s still living.

612
00:49:07,040 --> 00:49:10,360
Honestly, what have you been lying to me?

613
00:49:23,320 --> 00:49:26,320
I lied about being an interior designer.

614
00:49:28,600 --> 00:49:31,240
I do have a degree,

615
00:49:31,840 --> 00:49:35,440
but I never quite got to work
in that field of expertise.

616
00:49:38,360 --> 00:49:39,920
I’m not polite, calm,

617
00:49:39,920 --> 00:49:42,080
or remotely gentlemanly.

618
00:49:43,720 --> 00:49:47,560
That was just a character
I created to gain your trust.

619
00:49:53,840 --> 00:49:57,680
But that wasn’t the case at the end.

620
00:49:59,800 --> 00:50:00,880
What do you mean?

621
00:50:02,760 --> 00:50:05,800
I let my true colors slip out
when I was with you.

622
00:50:09,040 --> 00:50:13,440
It got harder and harder to stop myself
when I fell in love with you.

623
00:50:17,240 --> 00:50:20,920
If you don’t love me, don’t say that.

624
00:50:26,560 --> 00:50:27,480
Pai.

625
00:50:28,960 --> 00:50:30,960
I really am in love with you.

626
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:39,080
Maybe not from the first moment we met,

627
00:50:40,640 --> 00:50:42,920
but I am in love with you.

628
00:51:02,720 --> 00:51:04,800
I know I was wrong for what happened.

629
00:51:06,800 --> 00:51:07,800
I’m sorry.

630
00:51:13,320 --> 00:51:17,760
Don’t think I’ll forgive you
just because I agreed to stay at your place.

631
00:51:24,240 --> 00:51:26,400
I’m not giving up on you.

632
00:51:26,800 --> 00:51:29,320
Just watch out and try not to fall for me.

633
00:51:32,320 --> 00:51:33,560
Be my guest.

634
00:51:36,800 --> 00:51:37,920
Well, I did ask.

635
00:51:47,320 --> 00:51:49,600
Gecko!

636
00:51:49,600 --> 00:51:50,600
Where?
Where’s the gecko?

637
00:51:51,320 --> 00:51:52,880
There it is!

638
00:51:53,360 --> 00:51:54,440
Did you lie to me?

639
00:51:54,440 --> 00:51:55,200
Aren’t you a fighter?
Fight me.

640
00:51:56,080 --> 00:51:56,680
Fight me!

641
00:51:56,840 --> 00:51:57,840
Let go of me!

642
00:51:57,840 --> 00:51:59,240
Why don’t you fight me back?

643
00:51:59,240 --> 00:52:00,160
North!
Don’t bother North.

644
00:52:01,640 --> 00:52:02,320
Help!

645
00:52:02,680 --> 00:52:03,240
Mr. Pai?
Pai?

646
00:52:09,400 --> 00:52:10,840
It’s just some ghosts, North.

647
00:52:11,200 --> 00:52:12,000
Let’s go back to bed.
Hold on.

648
00:52:13,440 --> 00:52:14,640
North can’t help you.

649
00:52:14,880 --> 00:52:16,080
Don’t you see that he’s sleeping?

650
00:52:17,280 --> 00:52:17,840
Hey!
Hey!

651
00:52:20,280 --> 00:52:22,560
I guess North really can’t help
since he’s sleeping.

652
00:52:23,120 --> 00:52:24,160
Just take North to bed, U.

653
00:52:24,160 --> 00:52:25,400
I can exorcise this ghost on my own.

654
00:52:25,880 --> 00:52:26,440
Wait.

655
00:52:28,320 --> 00:52:29,000
- Let’s go.
- No way.
U!

656
00:52:30,560 --> 00:52:31,160
Hold on!

657
00:52:31,800 --> 00:52:32,400
U!

658
00:52:32,960 --> 00:52:33,480
U!

659
00:52:46,640 --> 00:52:49,440
If it’s just about money,
I’ll agree to a divorce.

660
00:52:49,440 --> 00:52:52,440
But can we share a nice meal
one last time?

661
00:52:53,360 --> 00:52:55,280
Why are you still seeing U, North?

662
00:52:55,280 --> 00:52:57,360
If he wanted to fool me,
he would have run.

663
00:52:57,360 --> 00:52:59,840
It must be love if he chose to stay.

664
00:52:59,840 --> 00:53:01,000
It’s a shame.

665
00:53:01,000 --> 00:53:03,200
I would have loved to meet him
one more time.

666
00:53:03,360 --> 00:53:04,400
You mean the Tim you knew?

667
00:53:04,880 --> 00:53:05,520
Yeah.
Alright.

668
00:53:11,080 --> 00:53:12,440
Hey, baby.

